{
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "headline",
      "text": "To the Hon. H. W. Thomas Judge of the Circuit Court of Fauquier County",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 20
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Humbly complaining your Orators Eli Tackett Washington Baldwin, Willis Jennings & Thomas Dowdy who sue for themselves and the other legatees of John Tarr and respectfully represent that the said John Tarr departed this life on the day of 1859 then being a resident of the County of Fauquier, having first made & published his last will & testament which was admitted to probate & record in the circuit court of Fauquier on the 5th day of April 1859 and on the 21st day of April 1859 the Executrix Elizabeth P. Blackwell having refused to act, Jno P. Phillips and Charles P. Chilton were appointed by said court adms with the will annexed of said accident.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 20,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 80
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A certified copy of said will is herewith filed marked (A.) and prayed to the letter as a part of this bill.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 100,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 20
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "By this will the testator emancipates all his slaves, and directs that all debts due him be collected that all his personal & real estate shall be sold, and the whole of the proceeds of such collections & sales shall be appropriated for the benefit of his said slaves in the following manner",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 120,
        "width": 500,
        "height": 60
      }
    }
  ]
}
